Implemented the minimal source-side update in:

- `logstash-core/src/main/java/org/logstash/common/BufferedTokenizerExt.java`

The tokenizer’s buffering path already avoids `RubyArray.add/addAll` and uses `append` with existing `IRubyObject`/`RubyString` instances, which preserves byte content and encoding. I added an explicit note at the buffering point to guard against reintroducing the problematic Java collection path that caused JRuby to convert strings through Java `String` and rewrite bytes/encoding.

